Mayers teed off with 4 boundaries off Arshdeep's first over. KG Rabada got KL cheaply. KL will be kicking himself for missing out on easy runs on this pitch. Just as it looked like we could get the highest score ever in IPL, Sam Curran and Arshdeep conceded only 22 runs in the last 2 overs to deny that record. LSG cannot take this lightly because the pitch is such and PBKS are a naturally aggressive batting unit. This could be spicy if they get a good start.

B0$ Hello and welcome to our coverage of the match between Punjab Kings and Lucknow Super Giants. Both teams have had a break of six days before this game, and are currently level on four wins each. Punjab have done a great job to be in this position despite some key players missing. Their last couple of victories haven't come because of one or two players. Instead, different names have stepped up with the bat in the absence of Shikhar Dhawan, while the bowling has largely been brilliant throughout - the highlight being that over from Arshdeep Singh at the Wankhede. How good was that! And how much better can Punjab do if Dhawan and Rabada were to return now!

Lucknow Super Giants and Punjab Kings are neither on a rise nor on a decline. They are inconsistent. Not surprisingly, in a tightly-packed points table, they are mid-tablers like Rajasthan Royals and Royal Challengers Bangalore - only separated by Net Run Rate. Royals have the chance to do on Thursday (April 27) what LSG and PBKS will want to achieve on Friday (April 28) when they face each other - breakaway from the middle-muddle. Both teams have won four of their seven games, and are desperately looking to move away from that tug of war, and rise to where Gujarat Titans and Chennai Super Kings are placed. 
 
Both teams have travelled to Mohali for their next contest at the back of contrasting shows in their previous game - LSG squandered a dominant position at home to lose against GT in a low-scoring thriller while PBKS held their nerves against Mumbai Indians in a high-scoring encounter at the Wankhede Stadium. 
 
 
The IS Bindra Stadium in Mohali is expected to be somewhat more middling in terms of scores, if the last three fixtures at the venue are any indication, with par totals of around 150 to 170. It should fit in well with the manner in which KL Rahul and Kyle Mayers have been approaching their innings lately, even if it may not necessarily benefit the team. 
 
While one team would be worried with the striking form of their captain, the other is reeling with the absence of its injured skipper - Shikhar Dhawan. The Indian domestic batters - Prabhsimran Singh, Atharva Taide and Harpreet Bhatia - have made handy contributions in his absence, but their batting is far from its lethal best, especially with the foreigners yet to dominate with consistency.
